#: src/code_of_conduct.md:1
msgid "Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:3
msgid ""
"We are committed to providing a friendly, safe and welcoming environment for "
"all, regardless of level of experience, gender identity and expression, "
"sexual orientation, disability, personal appearance, body size, race, "
"ethnicity, age, religion, nationality, or other similar characteristic."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:4
msgid ""
"Use of so-called Artificial Intelligence (AI) is allowed only if it is "
"explicitly mentioned. Additionally all LLM-generated text or code must be "
"manually reviewed by the author before submission (no vibe coding allowed)."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:5
msgid ""
"Please avoid using overtly sexual aliases or other nicknames that might "
"detract from a friendly, safe and welcoming environment for all."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:6
msgid "Please be kind and courteous. There’s no need to be mean or rude."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:7
msgid ""
"Respect that people have differences of opinion and that every design or "
"implementation choice carries a trade-off and numerous costs. There is "
"seldom a right answer."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:8
msgid ""
"Please keep unstructured critique to a minimum. If you have solid ideas you "
"want to experiment with, make a fork and see how it works."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:9
msgid ""
"We will exclude you from interaction if you insult, demean or harass anyone. "
"That is not welcome behavior. We interpret the term “harassment” as "
"including the definition in the [Citizen Code of Conduct](https://github.com/"
"stumpsyn/policies/blob/master/citizen_code_of_conduct.md); if you have any "
"lack of clarity about what might be included in that concept, please read "
"their definition. In particular, we don’t tolerate behavior that excludes "
"people in socially marginalized groups."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:10
msgid ""
"Private harassment is also unacceptable. No matter who you are, if you feel "
"you have been or are being harassed or made uncomfortable by a community "
"member, please contact one of the channel ops or any of the Lemmy moderation "
"team immediately. Whether you’re a regular contributor or a newcomer, we "
"care about making this community a safe place for you and we’ve got your "
"back."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:11
msgid ""
"Likewise any spamming, trolling, flaming, baiting or other attention-"
"stealing behavior is not welcome."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:12
msgid ""
"[Entitlement](https://tylercipriani.com/blog/2023/01/15/entitlement-burnout-"
"and-toxicity/), ie demanding or insulting behavior towards someone for not "
"doing what you want them to do, or not doing it fast enough, will also not "
"be tolerated."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:14
msgid ""
"[**Message the Moderation Team on Mastodon**](https://mastodon.social/"
"@LemmyDev)"
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:16
msgid "Moderation"
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:18
msgid ""
"These are the policies for upholding our community’s standards of conduct. "
"If you feel that a thread needs moderation, please contact the Lemmy "
"moderation team ."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:20
msgid ""
"Remarks that violate the Lemmy standards of conduct, including hateful, "
"hurtful, oppressive, or exclusionary remarks, are not allowed. (Cursing is "
"allowed, but never targeting another user, and never in a hateful manner.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:21
msgid ""
"Remarks that moderators find inappropriate, whether listed in the code of "
"conduct or not, are also not allowed."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:22
msgid ""
"Moderators will first respond to such remarks with a warning, at the same "
"time the offending content will likely be removed whenever possible."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:23
msgid ""
"If the warning is unheeded, the user will be “kicked,” i.e., kicked out of "
"the communication channel to cool off."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:24
msgid ""
"If the user comes back and continues to make trouble, they will be banned, i."
"e., indefinitely excluded."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:25
msgid ""
"Moderators may choose at their discretion to un-ban the user if it was a "
"first offense and they offer the offended party a genuine apology."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:26
msgid ""
"If a moderator bans someone and you think it was unjustified, please take it "
"up with that moderator, or with a different moderator, in private. "
"Complaints about bans in-channel are not allowed."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:27
msgid ""
"Moderators are held to a higher standard than other community members. If a "
"moderator creates an inappropriate situation, they should expect less leeway "
"than others."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:29
msgid ""
"In the Lemmy community we strive to go the extra step to look out for each "
"other. Don’t just aim to be technically unimpeachable, try to be your best "
"self. In particular, avoid flirting with offensive or sensitive issues, "
"particularly if they’re off-topic; this all too often leads to unnecessary "
"fights, hurt feelings, and damaged trust; worse, it can drive people away "
"from the community entirely."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:31
msgid ""
"And if someone takes issue with something you said or did, resist the urge "
"to be defensive. Just stop doing what it was they complained about and "
"apologize. Even if you feel you were misinterpreted or unfairly accused, "
"chances are good there was something you could’ve communicated better — "
"remember that it’s your responsibility to make others comfortable. Everyone "
"wants to get along and we are all here first and foremost because we want to "
"talk about cool technology. You will find that people will be eager to "
"assume good intent and forgive as long as you earn their trust."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:33
msgid ""
"The enforcement policies listed above apply to all official Lemmy venues; "
"including git repositories under [github.com/LemmyNet](https://github.com/"
"LemmyNet) and [git.join-lemmy.org/LemmyNet](https://git.join-lemmy.org/"
"LemmyNet/), the [Matrix chat](https://matrix.to/#/#lemmy-space:matrix.org); "
"[lemmy.ml](https://lemmy.ml) and other instances under that domain. For "
"other projects adopting the Lemmy Code of Conduct, please contact the "
"maintainers of those projects for enforcement. If you wish to use this code "
"of conduct for your own project, consider explicitly mentioning your "
"moderation policy or making a copy with your own moderation policy so as to "
"avoid confusion."
msgstr ""

#: src/code_of_conduct.md:35
msgid ""
"Adapted from the [Rust Code of Conduct](https://www.rust-lang.org/policies/"
"code-of-conduct), which is based on the [Node.js Policy on Trolling](http://"
"blog.izs.me/post/30036893703/policy-on-trolling) as well as the [Contributor "
"Covenant v1.3.0](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/1/3/0/)."
msgstr ""
